OL,3,CShould new drivers face tighter
OL,4,Crestrictions after 6,000 serious
OL,5,Ccrashes?
OL,7,FIn 2022, 29,742 people were killed or
OL,8,Fseriously injured on our roads, around
OL,9,F6,000 of those involved cars driven by
OL,10,Fa young car driver.
OL,12,FDrivers under 25 make up only 6% of
OL,13,Fdrivers in the UK ` but account for
OL,14,Fone in every five serious or fatal
OL,15,Fcrashes, according to the RAC.
OL,17,FBut the only difference for new
OL,18,Fdrivers is they can have their licence
OL,19,Frevoked if they receive six penalty
OL,20,Fpoints within their first two years.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/12
